DurbanÂ - The driver of a bakkie that allegedly lost control of the vehicle and slammed into the concrete pillars of the St Johns bridge in Pinetown is still in a critical condition in hospital on Tuesday. The bakkie struck the bridge pillar on the centre median of the M13 Durban bound on Monday afternoon. Garrith Jamieson, operations manager for Rescue Care Paramedics, said when they arrived on the scene they found an extensively damaged vehicle against the bridge. "The driver and only occupant in the vehicle had sustained critical injuries and needed Advanced Life Support Paramedics to stabilise him on the scene. Once the man was stabilised on the scene, he was rushed to a nearby hospital for the further care that he required. At this stage the events leading up to the collision is unknown however the necessary authorities were on the scene and will be investigating further," Jamieson explained. Daily News  